01/04/2011
BERLIN, Germany -- Chancellor Angela Merkel reaffirmed on Thursday (March 31st) that the future for Western Balkan countries lies in the EU and there is no enlargement fatigue.
After meeting Montenegrin Prime Minister Igor Luksic in Berlin she said Montenegro has to meet several criteria set by the European Commission before it can advance in the EU integration process.
Luksic briefed the German chancellor about steps the country is taking to meet EU membership criteria.
(RTCG, Portal Analitika, Antena M, Mina - 31/03/11)
